  <title>Gio.Mount.prototype.get_drive</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function get_drive(): <link xref="Gio.Drive">Gio.Drive</link> {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_mount_get_drive()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Gets the drive for the <code>mount</code>.</p>  <p>This is a convenience method for getting the <link xref="Gio.Volume"/> and then
using that object to get the <link xref="Gio.Drive"/>.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p>a <link xref="Gio.Drive"/> or <code>null</code> if <code>mount</code> is not associated with a volume or a drive.
     The returned object should be unreffed with
     <link href="../GObject-2.0/GObject.Object.unref.html">GObject.Object.prototype.unref</link> when no longer needed.</p>
</item>
